<item>
            <title>[PDFBOX-2156] different shading patterns at different resolutions when ctm is null</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/PDFBOX-2156</link>
                <project id="12310760" key="PDFBOX">PDFBox</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The attached file renders incorrectly except at 72dpi; at other resolutions, there are different results that get worse as the resolution gets higher. For shading types 2 and 3, this effect happens only in the 1.8 versions, not in the 2.0 version. For shading types 4 and up, it happens in both 1.8 and 2.0.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The reason is that the transformation is incomplete if the ctm is null.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I found the file here and it was created by Matthias Kramm:&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/jdapena/swftools/tree/master/spec&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://github.com/jdapena/swftools/tree/master/spec&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
